						| std::string Member Functions |
						 -----------------------------

Input/Output Functions
-----------------------
push_back(): Inserts a character at the end of the string.
pop_back(): Removes the last character from the string.


Capacity Functions
------------------
size(): Returns the number of characters in the string.
length(): Returns the number of characters in the string.
capacity(): Returns the maximum number of characters that can be stored in the string without increasing its memory allocation.
max_size(): Returns the maximum number of characters that can be stored in the string.
resize(): Changes the size of the string, either truncating characters from the end or inserting new characters.
reserve(): Requests a change in capacity.


Access Functions
-----------------
at(): Returns a reference to the character at a specified position in the string.
operator[](): Returns a reference to the character at a specified position in the string.
front(): Returns a reference to the first character in the string.
back(): Returns a reference to the last character in the string.
data(): Returns a pointer to the character array.
c_str(): Returns a pointer to the character array.


Modification Functions
-----------------------
assign(): Assigns a new value to the string.
append(): Appends characters to the end of the string.
insert(): Inserts characters into the string at a specified position.
erase(): Removes characters from the string.
replace(): Replaces characters in the string with new characters.
swap(): Swaps the contents of two strings.


Search Functions
-------------------
find(): Searches for a substring in the string.
rfind(): Searches for a substring in the string, starting from the end.
find_first_of(): Searches for the first occurrence of any character in a specified string.
find_last_of(): Searches for the last occurrence of any character in a specified string.
find_first_not_of(): Searches for the first occurrence of any character not in a specified string.
find_last_not_of(): Searches for the last occurrence of any character not in a specified string.


Comparison Functions
-----------------------
compare(): Compares the string with another string.
operator==(): Compares the string with another string.
operator!=(): Compares the string with another string.
operator<(): Compares the string with another string.
operator>(): Compares the string with another string.
operator<=(): Compares the string with another string.
operator>=(): Compares the string with another string.


Iterator Functions
-----------------------
begin(): Returns an iterator pointing to the beginning of the string.
end(): Returns an iterator pointing to the end of the string.
rbegin(): Returns a reverse iterator pointing to the end of the string.
rend(): Returns a reverse iterator pointing to the beginning of the string.
cbegin(): Returns a constant iterator pointing to the beginning of the string.
cend(): Returns a constant iterator pointing to the end of the string.
crbegin(): Returns a constant reverse iterator pointing to the end of the string.
crend(): Returns a constant reverse iterator pointing to the beginning of the string.


Miscellaneous Functions
-------------------------
empty(): Returns whether the string is empty.
clear(): Clears the contents of the string.
get_allocator(): Returns the allocator object used by the string.